<div class="articleBody">
        
    
                                                                                <p>
                    QURGHAN TAPA, Afghanistan &mdash; The hill wasn&rsquo;t much to behold, just a treeless mound of dirt barely 80 feet high. But for <a href="http://topics.nytimes.com/top/reference/timestopics/organizations/t/taliban/index.html?inline=nyt-org" title="More articles about the Taliban." class="meta-org">Taliban</a> fighters, it was a favorite spot for launching rockets into Imam Sahib city. Ideal, American commanders figured, for the insurgents to disrupt the coming parliamentary elections.        </p>
